sql:
SELECT sequence, molecular_weight
FROM peptides
WHERE bitter = 1 AND umami = 0;

SELECT DISTINCT u.user_name, u.email
FROM users AS u
WHERE u.is_active = 1 AND u.department = 'Bioinformatics' AND u.role = 'researcher';

SELECT sequence
FROM peptides
WHERE hydrophobicity = (SELECT MAX(hydrophobicity) FROM peptides);

SELECT AVG(molecular_weight) AS average_molecular_weight
FROM peptides
WHERE bitter = 1 AND citation_count > 10;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM project_peptides 
WHERE project_id = 'project_id_number';

external_knowledge:
- Highly preferred peptides: Priority > 5;
- Very strong taste intensities: Taste score > 7;
- Bitter and umami peptides: Peptides that have both bitter and umami taste attributes;
- Preference level: Indicates the importance of the peptide in its project.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM projects 
WHERE lead_user_id = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE user_name = 'Alice Johnson');

SELECT project_id, peptide_id, status
FROM project_peptides
WHERE priority > 2;

SELECT sequence
FROM peptides
WHERE bitter = 1 AND umami = 1 AND hydrophobicity < 0.5;

SELECT taste_type, COUNT(*) 
FROM taste_profiles 
GROUP BY taste_type;

external_knowledge:
- "frequently mentioned" refers to peptides accessed more than once;
- "contact details" in the context of users include the email addresses of the users;
- "top three peptides by access count" means the peptides with the highest number of access entries.
